My advice would be to start out with easy plants, so that you don't get discouraged if you fail. Pea shoots should be fairly easy, with a decent harvest and short time from planting to harvesting, so might be worth trying something like that, if you want some easy to grow greens. The whole plant above the soil can be used in salads, and tastes slightly like peas :)


For fertilizer, I would look into natural ones, like egg shells, coffee grinds and banana peel tea (which I've never tried, but sounds interesting). Other than that, just have fun, and enjoy your gardening yourney! :D
